Description:
A picture-perfect hideaway, bright and well-positioned
Tucked away at the end of a cul de sac, this pretty period cottage is a perfect choice for professional singles and couples. Filled with light, immaculately maintained and with potential for an upper-level extension (STCA) the home, set behind a high picket fence and verandah, comprises one double bedroom (BIRs and ceiling fan), a good-sized living/dining room open to a well-equipped kitchen, plus updated bathroom/laundry. Moments from Smith Street cafes, boutiques and CBD transport, it opens to a delightful slate-paved al fresco entertaining courtyard. Features include timber floors, plaster detail and split-system air conditioning.
Insights: 2 Emma Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2020.

Description:
A stellar display of style, luxury, views & balconies
Peel by Milieu is DKO Architecture's acclaimed boutique building, and a sought-after inner Melbourne favourite, where this stunning multi-balcony apartment savours brilliant views. A breathtaking outlook encompassing historic landmarks, Kew's Studley Park and the Dandenong Ranges is your wake-up call while Mr Peel cafe and Congress wine bar below will get you going into a sensational city-fringe groove with this high-end designer apartment. Large double-glazed windows, muted oak floors and in-situ concrete ceilings frame ultra-stylish spaces enhanced by heating/cooling, copious custom storage and 2 alfresco areas including semi-enclosed entertainment terrace. There are 2 robed bedrooms (main with seat window views), open-plan living and dining room with full-height sliding door, luxury Smeg-appointed kitchen with stainless-steel countertops and integrated fridge/freezer, bar unit, chic contemporary bathroom, laundry plus video intercom, bicycle space and storage cage on title and lift access. Step out in style and stroll to the Smith/Brunswick/Gertrude Streets' quarter, trams, Fitzroy Gardens, MCG, East Melbourne hospitals and the CBD.
Insights: 604/47 Peel Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2020 and 83 other 2 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Designer luxury lifestyle with breathtaking city views
The city skyline creates an endless, uninterrupted, breathtaking backdrop for this stunning apartment in the luxurious milieu of John Wardle Architects' exclusive new Holme. Rising with sculptural poise from its Art Deco warehouse heritage, the dynamic Holme building with its 240 sqm communal kitchen, fireside lounge, teppanyaki grill and garden area is the magnificent city-edge setting for this elegant contemporary apartment. Double-glazing, oak flooring and high clean-lined ceilings define the sophisticated spaces of the brilliant single-level interior opening through full-height doors to an undercover terrace designed for spectacular city-view alfresco entertaining. A versatile dining room or home office adds a desirable dimension complementing a beautiful bedroom (mirror BIRs, sliding door to terrace), open-plan living and dining room and designer kitchen showcasing high-end ASKO appliances. There's also a streamlined bathroom, laundry, heating/cooling, NBN, storage cage and secure car space on title. Located right by East Melbourne within easy walking distance to cafes, restaurants and shops including Gertrude Street, art galleries, Fitzroy Gardens, MCG, hospitals and the CBD.
Insights: 713/68 Cambridge Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2020 and 49 other 1 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
World-class warehouse of compelling space & luxury
Inner-Melbourne's premier warehouse precinct in the oldest of the historic Foy & Gibson buildings (1887) is crowned by this spectacular residence that's staged over 3 compelling levels under a towering 10m Oregon-trussed ceiling. World-class in its breathtaking design, high-end quality and bespoke brilliance; this is a conversion for the ages highlighting its rich industrial aesthetic with uncompromising flair. A vast, light-capturing void is the centrepiece of this remarkable achievement in city-edge architectural excellence designed for inspirational indoor-outdoor living and entertaining. Featuring a rooftop deck plus sunroom opening to a large secluded terrace, open-plan living and dining areas defined by tall windows and exposed quadruple-brick walls lead to a luxury custom-built kitchen including Neff self-cleaning pyrolytic ovens, ASKO gas/induction cooktop, Italian Fenix benchtops, rolled steel island and butler's pantry. There's a mezzanine library, 2 huge bedrooms with WIRs and ensuites, study or 3rd bedroom, 2 king-size loft spaces plus powder room, full laundry, storeroom, ducted heating, a/c, Baltic pine floors and secure car space. This completely secure, one-of-a-kind warehouse residence offers a sensational, low-maintenance lifestyle in the Smith-Brunswick-Gertrude Streets' gourmet and culture precinct near East Melbourne hospitals, Fitzroy and Carlton Gardens, the MCG and CBD.
Insights: 18/79 Oxford Street, Collingwood VIC 3066 was last sold in 2020 and 18 other 3 bedroom unit in Collingwood have recently been sold.

Description:
Outstanding opportunity in the heart of Collingwood
Commanding a prominent address in the heart of Collingwood's popular arts precinct, this double storey home offers enormous potential to renovate or redevelop (STCA). It occupies approx. 246sqm with three frontages on the corner of Sackville Street and is strolling distance to vibrant Smith Street, Abbotsford village and Victoria Park station. Boasting generous proportions throughout, the existing residence reveals a huge front bedroom with an open fireplace, master bedroom with built-ins and an ensuite, and third robed bedroom. Further on is a spacious living and dining area with a gas fireplace, functional gas kitchen with a dishwasher, and bathroom with a bath, shower and separate w/c. Upstairs are two light filled bedrooms with wall-to-wall built-ins. Outside is a large north facing courtyard with ROW access to a single carport, and substantial separate studio. In addition, it features high ceilings and timber floors. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

NYC Inspired Warehouse Living
Located in vibrant Oxford St, the warehouse capital of Melbourne, this stunning split level Edgard Pirrota designed warehouse loft has remained true to its NYC inspirations. A simple two level layout allows for light and lofty warehouse living blended with original features as well as modern appointment. Simply put everything you would expect from a contemporary residence! Comprises huge open plan living and delightful courtyard terrace, large kitchen area, separate laundry and downstairs powder room with upstairs accommodation by way of super-sized master bedroom with WIR's and ensuite, good sized second bedroom and purpose built study area. Other stand-out features include off street parking, security entry, hydronic heating, split system AC in bedrooms & living. Moments from Gertrude, Smith & Brunswick Streets with easy CBD and public transport access close by.

Description:
Historic Collingwood residence with great potential
A fantastic opportunity has arisen to secure a slice of Collingwood's history with this c1861 residence boasting two street frontages and ROW access. Defined by generous original proportions, it presents comfortable light filled interiors with retained period character and scope to renovate (STCA). It is also ideally placed just a short stroll to Abbotsford village, Collingwood's restaurant precinct, Victoria Park station, bus transport and Yarra Bend parklands, and provides easy access to the M3 and Hoddle Street for city commuters. Beyond its striking solid brick façade with arched windows, the entrance hall leads to three huge bedrooms including one with a decorative fireplace. Further on is a spacious central living room, dining area and functional gas kitchen with stainless steel fixtures. Nearby is a bright bathroom with a clawfoot bath and shower. Step outdoors to a large private bluestone courtyard, separate workshop and single lock-up garage with access via Perry Street. It features hydronic heating throughout, split system a/c, soaring ceilings and a Bosch security system. Nelson Alexander Pty Ltd

Description:
Wake up to the Morning Sun
This east facing apartment is approximately 71 sqm internally, featuring:
- Large windows allowing natural light into the living space
- Study area in living area
- Timber floorboards in main areas
- Reconstituted stone bench tops
- Semi frameless glass shower screens
- Stainless steel cooktop, oven, dishwasher
- Wide balcony from living area
- Separate 'smokers' balcony from master bedroom
If you are searching in this area, you would already know that living in Collingwood is a lifestyle choice. Think thick cut bacon brunch, hip culture, single origin coffees and award-winning bars. This is walking distance to the city, healthcare centres, peppered by the convenience of public transport, the Eastern Freeway and not too far away from the Yarra Boulevard for those keen for a bike ride or jog.
This apartment belongs to the Yorkshire Brewery development completed a few years ago tucked away into Collingwoods' laneways. Common amenities include an outdoor BBQ area, a quiet library to watch cat videos on your iPad, a small gym - good for those morning yoga sessions and a dining area / function room to entertain your guests.
OC fees are approximately $3800 per annum. Currently tenanted at $550pw.
Whilst all care has been taken to write this advertisement, buyers need to do their own due diligence and assessment before purchasing.

Description:
Stanley Stunner!
***IMPORTANT***
Given current concerns regarding COVID-19, Melbourne Real Estate are now conducting one on one inspections of properties only to qualified buyers. After assessing if the property suits your needs based on the photos, floorplan and property description, you can book a private inspection by clicking the Book An Inspection link on this listing. A sales agent from Melbourne Real Estate will be in contact with you prior to the inspection to discuss the property, ensuring it meets your buying requirements before confirming the appointment.
We thank you for your patience while we take these added precautionary measures in an effort to restrict the spread of COVID-19.
Your inner-north city pad awaits! Located on Stanley Street within close proximity to Smith Street, Coles, cafes, restaurants and a plethora of public transport options, this apartment is not to be missed! Positioned in a boutique block of only 40 apartments, this property features:
Kitchen with stainless steel appliances, including a four burner cooktop, rangehood, dishwasher and oven. Storage and space are plentiful with a large island bench doubling as a dining table.
Open plan living with high exposed-concrete ceiling, track lighting, reverse cycle air-conditioning and timber floors throughout. Floor to ceiling windows onto the balcony allow for plenty of natural light.
A large tiled balcony hosts a perfect spot to unwind with a glass of wine at the end of the day.
Carpeted master bedroom has a large built in wardrobe and floor to ceiling windows. The second room can be used as a bedroom or study area.
Main bathroom featuring an exposed brick finish, floor to ceiling tiles and plenty of storage throughout.
This apartment is currently leased on a fixed term tenancy until 06/10/2020 achieving $475 per week.
Well thought out apartments in highly desirable locations dont last long!

Description:
Boutique and Brilliant
Exceeding expectations, this light filled, contemporary edged, elevated two bedroom apartment is a true surprise packet. The key to the apartment are the huge windows and soaring ceilings - which define the living space - and ensure the apartment is a delight to enjoy all year round. Only one of six in a boutique block, the apartment is fully updated and renovated. There are also a number of new quality inclusions such as the polished timber floorboards, fully tiled designer bathroom, as well as a magnificent newly renovated kitchen with tonnes of storage and bench space ideal for five star cooking. Comprises 2 bedrooms, central bathroom, abundant open plan living, gorgeous terrace with delightful outlook, off street parking, storage locker and more. Moments from Smith, Gertrude and Brunswick Streets - but set in a surprisingly quiet inner city location.

Description:
Parkview Heights Exclusive
Centrally positioned right in the heart of the Inner North, is this tranquil light filled private residence.
Tucked away on the first floor, at the rear of this boutique block of only 6, the apartment showcases a smart open plan living/dining with gas heating, split system cooling and 2 spacious bedrooms with built in robes.
Featuring an inviting kitchen with gas cooking, dishwasher, central bathroom, security entry with intercom and handy car park.
Fantastic urban location, taking full advantage of the culinary delights of popular local restaurants, cafes, bars and close to parkland, bike trails, galleries and clothing retailers.
Securely Leased at $1,999pcm until the 4th September, 2020.

ANOTHER SOLD BY TIM ~ THINKING OF SELLING? CALL TIM : 0449 998 787 FOR A FREE PROPERTY VALUATION ~ Another Record Price for the 107 Building!
ANOTHER SOLD BY TIM ~ THINKING OF SELLING? CALL TIM : 0449 998 787 FOR A FREE PROPERTY VALUATION ~ Another Record Price for the 107 Building!
Look no further! This fabulous modern, stylish, ground floor one-bedroom apartment plus a study! in arguably one of the best designed buildings in Collingwood is definitely a must see! A near new development in prime, city door-step location bordering East Melbourne, surrounded by cafes', restaurants and just metres from Collingwood's famous entertainment precinct, Smith Street and Johnston street shops with multiple train, bus and tram options for direct access into the CBD. Comprising of one large bedroom with connection to the courtyard area and semi-ensuite bathroom is so rare to find. The beautifully designed kitchen with high-end fixtures and fittings throughout brings style and class to the apartment with the adjoining spacious open plan design. The living area opens up onto a huge private and secluded courtyard area which creates indoor/outdoor living, perfect for entertaining with family and friends. Further offering a fully appointed kitchen with stone benches, dishwasher, rangehood, stainless steel gas cooking and ample pantry storage, bleached timber flooring, as well as one secure parking space, store room with bike rack storage. Enjoy the inner urban lifestyle to the fullest, where you can walk or ride to virtually everything you need. Step out and enjoy Collingwood's bustling entertainment precinct and then retreat home to relax in the spacious living and courtyard areas. Be quick to inspect, this unique property won't last long enquire today!
